  "name": "Obscuring Mist",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p>A stationary, misty vapor arises around the caster and obscures all sight, including special visions, beyond 5 feet but within an area of 25 by 20 by 10 feet. A creature 5 feet away has one-half concealment, and creatures farther away have total concealment.</p><p>A moderate wind (11+ mph) disperses the fog in 4 rounds. A strong wind (21+ mph) disperses the fog in 1 round. A fire spell burns away any fog within the spell's area of effect. This spell does not function underwater. The caster can move out of the mist once it is created.</p>",
